"from\": 1432, \"to\": 1453}, {\"ngram\": \"the conflict\", \"from\": 1459, \"to\": 1471}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The IOC previously said, externally it had been a target of \\\"fake news posts\\\" and \\\"fake information\\\" which had included a documentary series narrated by an AI-generated voice purporting to be Hollywood actor Tom Cruise.\", \"from\": 1485, \"to\": 1704, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1489, \"end\": 1492, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.619020095213542e-20, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1677, \"end\": 1686, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999985365761198, \"rank\": 1.2766646207998627e-06, \"text\": \"Hollywood\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1693, \"end\": 1703, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Cruise\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a target\", \"from\": 1533, \"to\": 1541}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"fake news posts\", \"from\": 1545, \"to\": 1561}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"fake information\", \"from\": 1567, \"to\": 1584}, {\"ngram\": \"a documentary series\", \"from\": 1605, \"to\": 1625}, {\"ngram\": \"an AI-generated voice\", \"from\": 1638, \"to\": 1659}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletes representing Russia and Belarus were banned from the Olympics following Russia's invasion of Ukraine in February 2022, but they can compete at the Paris Games as neutrals.\", \"from\": 1